Rio used to be a hip place until Harrah's bought it out.
I hadn't eaten here in a while and wasn't sure if it would still taste as good as before.
With a buy 1 entree get 1 free coupon, I thought I would take a chance.
I was not disappointed.
The appetizer Crab Cakes were light but flavorful.
The Grilled Beef Tenderloin ($36), although at medium well, was very tender.
It tasted so good that I didn't even ask for A-1 sauce!
The Grilled Salmon($28) was fresh and moist.
The chimichurri gave it enough flavor that I didn't have to use any tabasco sauce, either.
Since everything was a la carte, we also ordered a side of Sauteed Foraged Mushrooms ($8) to share.
It, too, was surprisingly good!
Service was attentive since there were only 5 tables with diners.
This is a small restaurant.
The decor and ambiance are not up to bar considering the prices of the food.
If you're trying to impress your date, this is probably not a place to take her/him.
However, if you want good food without the wait, you might give this place a try.

